# ===========================================================================
#  Repo scope: track ONLY Assets/Game (plus the two git config files).
#  Everything else — Library/, Temp/, ProjectSettings/, purchased packages
#  (CorgiEngine, 2D_Pack, Casual Game Sounds, Chars), Editor helper scripts —
#  is intentionally excluded.
# ===========================================================================

# 1) Ignore everything at the repo root by default.
/*

# 2) Re-include the git configuration files themselves.
!/.gitattributes
!/.gitignore
!/README.md

# 3) Re-open the path down to Assets/Game (and nothing else under Assets).
!/Assets/
/Assets/*
!/Assets/Game/
!/Assets/Game.meta

# Track the level generator tooling (under Assets/Editor/Coplay) so it is versioned with the project.
!/Assets/Editor/
/Assets/Editor/*
!/Assets/Editor/Coplay/
/Assets/Editor/Coplay/*
!/Assets/Editor/Coplay/BuildCorgiLevel.cs
!/Assets/Editor/Coplay/BuildCorgiLevel.cs.meta
!/Assets/Editor/Coplay/LevelGeneratorWindow.cs

# 4) Within Assets/Game, keep everything (scenes, prefabs, scripts, sprites...).
=======
!/Assets/Editor/Coplay/LevelGeneratorWindow.cs.meta

# 4) Within Assets/Game, keep everything (scenes, prefabs, scripts, sprites...).
=======

# 4) Within Assets/Game, keep everything (scenes, prefabs, scripts, sprites...).
#    (No further ignores here — full Game folder is tracked.)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Safety: standard Unity-generated junk, in case scope is ever widened.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
[Ll]ibrary/
[Tt]emp/
[Oo]bj/
[Bb]uild/
[Bb]uilds/
[Ll]ogs/
[Uu]ser[Ss]ettings/
[Mm]emoryCaptures/
*.csproj
*.sln
*.user
*.booproj
*.pidb
*.suo
.vs/
.idea/
.vsconfig
